Sentence: Ses02F_script02_1_M000 [005.2900-008.8900]: What time is it?
They're supposed to run around midnight.
Ses02F_script02_1_M001 [008.9000-013.0300]: This is great, isn't it?
Look at the night we've got here, couldn't be better.
Ses02F_script02_1_M002 [013.0700-019.1800]: I would have liked to have gone a little further up the coast to get away from the lights and the people, but I was afraid we'd miss it.
Ses02F_script02_1_M003 [019.2200-020.3100]: How you doing?
Ses02F_script02_1_M004 [021.4000-026.6500]: Is that--no--is that just foam?
I can't even tell.
Ses02F_script02_1_M005 [026.6900-031.4300]: Well, I guess we can tell, it probably isn't right?
Probably be unmistakable don't you think?
Ses02F_script02_1_M006 [031.4700-039.6900]: How you doing?
Aw, you know what I forgot?
I forgot to bring my flashlight.
Oh, how could I be so stupid?
I should've brought my flashlight.
Ses02F_script02_1_F001 [039.3900-040.5700]: What flashlight?
Ses02F_script02_1_M007 [041.2400-044.0500]: You know, the flashlight, the silver one.
There's only one isn't there?
Ses02F_script02_1_F002 [043.9900-045.7400]: That's not your flashlight.
It's mine too.
Ses02F_script02_1_F004 [049.8400-055.5900]: You kept saying my flashlight, if as if somehow it's just yours.
I mean is that supposed to make me feel?
Ses02F_script02_1_M010 [055.3700-062.4000]: Right, of course.
Our flashlight.
Mine and yours.
I mean, me flashlight is su flashlight naturally.
Ses02F_script02_1_M011 [062.5000-067.4800]: How could we forget to bring it?
I hope the moon stays out.
Ses02F_script02_1_M012 [068.1500-072.9000]: I wonder, do they always run during a full moon?
I can't remember if it was full last year.
Do you remember?
Do you want my jacket?
Oh, we should've brought the blanket.
Our blanket.
Ses02F_script02_1_M014 [080.2700-085.8500]: This is great, isn't it?
A six pack would be just the ticket right now.
Ses02F_script02_1_M015 [085.9000-091.2500]: I can't believe I forgot.
I'm like a kid.
It's amazing I got out of the house with my fly zipped.
Ses02F_script02_1_M016 [093.4500-098.2100]: You think they can hear us talk?
Or feel the vibrations in the sand when we move around?
Ses02F_script02_1_M017 [100.6000-102.0300]: Do you want my jacket?
Ses02F_script02_1_F007 [102.2100-104.8400]: It's after eleven, let's just go home.
Ses02F_script02_1_M018 [105.1600-111.8200]: Are you kidding?
We'd miss it.
We just got here.
What's the point of coming down here if we just turn around and go home.
Ses02F_script02_1_F008 [111.1200-113.5500]: There is no point in coming down here.
Ses02F_script02_1_F009 [113.9100-115.4000]: That's my point.
Ses02F_script02_1_M020 [115.1000-116.6000]: That's my point too.
No.
That's not my point.
The point is there's no point in coming down if we just leave.
Don't you want to see it?
Ses02F_script02_1_F011 [124.4400-126.1200]: Not particularly.
It's stupid.
Ses02F_script02_1_M023 [130.9200-136.8600]: Honey, this is a natural phenomenon.
I mean this only happens once a year, you know.
Ses02F_script02_1_M024 [136.8900-143.8500]: Think about the people in Kansas, they had to get plane tickets and hotel reservations to see this.
We live forty minutes away.
It's too good to pass up.
These little fish swim onto the beach, they flop around, and swim away.
And then they die.
Ses02F_script02_1_M025 [149.6700-159.0000]: Yeah, but that moment on the beach, is the highlight of their little lives.
All that flopping is laying eggs or what do you--spawning or mating.
I mean,
Ses02F_script02_1_M026 [159.0500-162.0100]: this is a big night for these guys.
Life's last orgy.
Ses02F_script02_1_F014 [161.3900-168.6000]: What are you so excited about?
I mean, it's not a moon landing we're talking about here.
It's fish.
It's a fish nobody even eats.
But it's fish that do something that none of the other fish do.
Like the swallows returning to Capistrano or the lemmings throwing themselves off the cliffs.
Ses02F_script02_1_M029 [179.6700-186.6100]: There's--there's a bit of the magic--some unexplainable here.
I don't see how you can not be interested.
The first time we came here, you said it was the best night of your life.

Ses02F_script02_1_M032 [194.8400-202.5300]: And last year, I remember specifically you were so excited to go that you stubbed your toe rushing me out of the house and didn't even notice until we got in the car.

Ses02F_script02_1_F018 [201.7700-211.4700]: Last year, you will also remember our shoes got wet, I got sand in my panties, you got a sore throat, we got in a big fight over nothing, and we didn't see the grunions.
Ses02F_script02_1_M033 [211.4300-213.0800]: We weren't in a good spot.
Ses02F_script02_1_F019 [212.7100-214.9300]: We didn't see them the first time either.
Ses02F_script02_1_M034 [214.5300-220.1000]: We just weren't in a good spot.
This is a much better spot.
Believe me, I've got good instincts for these things.
Ses02F_script02_1_M035 [220.6300-225.0800]: There is that--no that's just seaweed isn't it?
Ses02F_script02_1_M036 [225.1400-233.2600]: Oh man, this is great, isn't it?
I wouldn't miss this for anything.
Here, think about this, all right, I know you're not interested, but think about this.
Ses02F_script02_1_M037 [233.3800-239.7300]: Somewhere out there, this huge mass of silver fish swimming this way.
Ses02F_script02_1_M038 [240.0400-247.1500]: They don't know why, we don't know why.
Nobody sent them an invitation or a map, it wasn't a decision, just-

Ses02F_script02_1_M039 [247.1700-261.5400]: all as one, this time release instinctual little firecracker went off and they all turned and formed a line as long as the California coast and started swimming.
And they're swimming right now as if that's all that matters.
Ses02F_script02_1_M040 [261.7400-271.7000]: It's like single mindedness with no mind.
It's urgency that's pure urge.
They don't know what drives them.
They don't ask it a question or give it a name.
Ses02F_script02_1_M041 [271.7100-280.1800]: They just turn as one and start the swim that brings them right here to where we stand, for a massive celebration of sex and death.
Ses02F_script02_1_M042 [280.2100-284.6400]: Ah, God, I'm giving myself goose bumps.
Look, all my hairs are popped up.
Ses02F_script02_1_F020 [284.0400-285.6000]: That's the wind.
Ses02F_script02_1_M043 [285.9500-287.8700]: Well, so what do you think?
Ses02F_script02_1_M044 [288.8000-290.2900]: What I was saying.
Ses02F_script02_1_F022 [290.4400-291.8400]: It's ridiculous.
